First time using my flight benefits on two other airlines and the process was pretty seamless! The total cost of the flights were $270( $115 British Airways & $153 Turkish Airlines) and I really flew on the jumpseat, economy, and first class—so you really never know what could happen. Exploring Istanbul was such a flavorful experience—the food, the lifestyle, and architecture was all new to me and very rich in culture. 

The scary part about traveling alone is getting to the actual city center especially with a language barrier—but taxis are everywhere and will definitely try to get every cent that they can. Other then that—shopping and walking around felt very safe and comfortable for me. I made sure to dress ✨conservatively ✨ and enjoyed all the views along the way.
